# Premium Attendance System — Implementation Plan

## Goal
Redesign the attendance UX across Teacher, Student, and Admin roles to feel modern, trustworthy, and daily-usable — without rewriting the existing backend core (one Attendance doc per date+subject+section with records[] array and upsert).

---

## Attendance Flow Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph Teacher
        T1["Select Class"] --> T2["Start Attendance Session"]
        T2 --> T3{"Self-Marking Enabled?"}
        T3 -- Yes --> T4["Students mark on their devices"]
        T3 -- No --> T5["Teacher marks manually"]
        T4 --> T6["Timer counts down (30 min default)"]
        T6 --> T7["Auto-close self-marking"]
        T7 --> T8["Teacher reviews + fills gaps"]
        T5 --> T8
        T8 --> T9["Finalize & Lock"]
    end
    subgraph Student
        S1["Open Attendance Dashboard"] --> S2["Calendar Grid - month view"]
        S2 --> S3["Tap day → tooltip with subject/teacher/status"]
        S1 --> S4["Summary Ring - overall %"]
        S1 --> S5{"Self-Mark window open?"}
        S5 -- Yes --> S6["Tap 'Mark Present' button"]
        S5 -- No --> S7["View-only mode"]
    end
    subgraph Admin
        A1["Filter by date / class / subject"] --> A2["View all attendance records"]
        A2 --> A3["Edit individual student status with reason"]
        A2 --> A4["Lock / Unlock records"]
        A3 --> A5["Audit badge shown on edited records"]
    end
    T9 -.-> S2
    T9 -.-> A2
```

---

## Minimal Backend Additions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The core Attendance model (schema, upsert, records[] array) is **NOT changed**. We only add 3 lightweight fields.

### [MODIFY] [Attendance.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/models/Attendance.ts)

Add 3 optional fields to the existing schema (no migration needed — Mongoose ignores missing fields on old docs):

```diff
 records: [{
     student: { type: Schema.Types.ObjectId, ref: 'User', required: true },
     status: { type: String, enum: ['present', 'absent', 'late', 'excused'], default: 'present' },
-    remarks: { type: String }
+    remarks: { type: String },
+    marked_by: { type: String, enum: ['teacher', 'self', 'admin'], default: 'teacher' }
 }],
 is_locked: { type: Boolean, default: false },
+status: { type: String, enum: ['open', 'reviewing', 'finalized'], default: 'open' },
+self_mark_open: { type: Boolean, default: false },
+self_mark_deadline: { type: Date },
 marked_at: { type: Date, default: Date.now }
```

| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `status` | 3-state lifecycle: [open](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/components/layout/PublicNavbar.tsx#214-218) → `reviewing` → `finalized` |
| `self_mark_open` | `true` while students can mark themselves |
| `self_mark_deadline` | Auto-close timestamp (e.g. now + 30 min) |
| `records[].marked_by` | Audit trail: who actually marked this (`teacher`, `self`, [admin](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/api/admin/courses/route.ts#8-14)) |

